HEADWORD: Perforation
<hw>Per`fo*ra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>perforation</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of perforating,
or of boring or piercing through.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A hole made by boring or piercing; an
aperture.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Slender <xex>perforations</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perforative</ent>⟦br⟧
